The paper focuses on the design of efficient error-correcting codes for Quantum Key Distribution (QKD) systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of Raptor codes also involves coding theory (cs.IT) and the application of these codes in QKD systems involves quantum information (cs.QI). The optimization of degree distributions using linear programming involves computational complexity (cs.CC) and the simulation results involve numerical analysis (cs.NI).
